author: National Geographic
description:
With its scraggly fur and piercing gaze, the aye-aye has often been considered bad luck, but these misunderstood primates could be vital for conservation. Clove trees on the east coast of Madagascar have been ravaged by leaf miner larvae—which aye-ayes happen to be very good at hunting.  #PhotoArk

Narrated by Ryan Reynolds, #Underdogs streaming now on @disneyplus and @hulu.
title: Keep an eye out for an Aye-Aye!
